# D15_CRC_GDSC2_PHARMACOLOGY_v1
# Pre-registration: 100-node CRC structural z_dr × GDSC2 pharmacology correlation
# Date: 2026-06-07
# Status: PRE-REGISTERED — do not load GDSC2 COREAD data or compute correlations before this commit

## Scientific background

D14b produced a validated 100-node TCGA COAD multi-layer network with cancer-specific
coexpression (Layer B: 945 edges, 524 tumor samples). The z_dr values identify:
  - EGFR:   +2.411  (top structural DAMPER)
  - MDM2:   +1.267  (DAMPER, 3x confirmed)
  - CDK4:   +1.172  (DAMPER, 7x confirmed across cancers)
  - MAP2K1: -0.187  (near-zero — 16-node boundary condition)
  - PIK3CA: -0.256  (near-zero)
  - AKT1:   -1.833  (ANCHOR)
  - KRAS:   -1.329  (ANCHOR)
  - BRAF:   -1.591  (ANCHOR)
  - MTOR:   -2.257  (strongest ANCHOR)
  - TP53:   -2.380  (strong ANCHOR)

These structural positions were computed from TCGA COAD tumor tissue (state-conditioned
Layer B). The pharmacological question is: does this 100-node structural ranking predict
drug sensitivity in CRC cell lines?

D3_CRC_v1 answered this for the 16-node network (Spearman r = -0.715 in PRISM). D15
answers it for the 100-node network using GDSC2, a different pharmacological assay
(multi-point IC50 dose-curve), at larger scale. This is the direct pharmacological
validation of the D14b structural findings.

## Data

GDSC2: GDSC2_fitted_dose_response_27Oct23.xlsx
  - Column TCGA_DESC: cancer type filter = "COREAD"
  - Column DRUG_NAME: drug identity
  - Column LN_IC50: natural log IC50 (uM); lower = more sensitive
  - Column CELL_LINE_NAME: cell line identity

D14b z_dr source: research/D14b_TCGA_COAD_FULL_results.md
  (100-node TCGA COAD, KRAS-WT+MT combined, 524 samples)

## Drug-target mapping (pre-registered, fixed before analysis)

Only drugs whose primary target has a D14b z_dr value are included.
Multi-target drugs included only if one target clearly dominates (noted below).
Antibody drugs excluded (not in GDSC2).

| Drug (GDSC2 name)  | Primary target | z_dr (D14b) |
|--------------------|---------------|-------------|
| Erlotinib          | EGFR          | +2.411      |
| Gefitinib          | EGFR          | +2.411      |
| Lapatinib          | EGFR          | +2.411      |
| Afatinib           | EGFR          | +2.411      |
| Osimertinib        | EGFR          | +2.411      |
| Palbociclib        | CDK4          | +1.172      |
| Abemaciclib        | CDK4          | +1.172      |
| Ribociclib         | CDK4          | +1.172      |
| Selumetinib        | MAP2K1        | -0.187      |
| Trametinib         | MAP2K1        | -0.187      |
| PD0325901          | MAP2K1        | -0.187      |
| Everolimus         | MTOR          | -2.257      |
| Temsirolimus       | MTOR          | -2.257      |
| Ipatasertib        | AKT1          | -1.833      |
| Capivasertib       | AKT1          | -1.833      |
| Copanlisib         | PIK3CA        | -0.256      |
| Alpelisib          | PIK3CA        | -0.256      |
| GDC-0941           | PIK3CA        | -0.256      |
| Vemurafenib        | BRAF          | -1.591      |
| Dabrafenib         | BRAF          | -1.591      |

Note: If a drug name in GDSC2 differs slightly (e.g. case, hyphen), the closest
unambiguous match is used and noted in results. Drugs not found in GDSC2 are excluded
from correlation and their absence reported. Minimum n = 10 drug-data-points required
for Spearman correlation; if fewer drugs found, H1 is flagged as underpowered.

## Analysis protocol (pre-registered)

1. Load GDSC2_fitted_dose_response_27Oct23.xlsx
2. Filter to TCGA_DESC == "COREAD"
3. For each drug in the mapping table above:
   a. Extract all COREAD LN_IC50 values for that drug
   b. Compute median LN_IC50 (one value per drug)
   c. Record n (number of cell lines with data)
   d. Flag drugs with n < 3 as insufficient
4. Build correlation dataset: (z_dr_target, median_LN_IC50) pairs across all drugs
   with n >= 3 cell lines
5. Compute Spearman r and two-sided p-value across all drug pairs
6. Compute Spearman r restricted to DAMPER drugs (z_dr > 0) only
7. Compute Spearman r restricted to ANCHOR drugs (z_dr < 0) only

Additionally: targeted group tests
- DAMPER_drugs = drugs with z_dr > 1.0 (EGFR, CDK4, MDM2 targets — if present)
- ANCHOR_drugs = drugs with z_dr < -1.0 (MTOR, AKT1, BRAF targets)
- Near-zero_drugs = drugs with |z_dr| < 0.5 (MAP2K1, PIK3CA targets)
  Test: median_LN_IC50(ANCHOR_drugs) vs median_LN_IC50(DAMPER_drugs) in COREAD
  — ANCHOR-targeting drugs should be less effective (higher LN_IC50) than DAMPER-targeting drugs

## Hypotheses

### H1: Spearman r(z_dr, median_LN_IC50_COREAD) < -0.3 across all mapped drugs
  Structural prediction: higher z_dr (structural DAMPER) → lower LN_IC50 (more sensitive)
  Threshold -0.3 chosen as minimum meaningful correlation (D3_CRC_v1 was -0.715 at 16 nodes;
  100-node network may show attenuated correlation due to multi-target effects)

  H1 CONFIRMED if: Spearman r < -0.3 AND p < 0.10 (directional, modest alpha given n)
  H1 DENIED if: r >= -0.3 OR p >= 0.10

### H2: MAP2K1 (MEK1) near-zero — MEK inhibitors show no predictive signal
  MAP2K1 z_dr = -0.187 at 100 nodes (near-zero). MEK inhibitors (selumetinib, trametinib,
  PD0325901) target MAP2K1. Prediction: median LN_IC50 of MEK inhibitors is NOT lower
  than the median of all tested drugs in COREAD.
  The D3_CRC_v1 result (MEK1 DAMPER at 16 nodes predicting MEK sensitivity) should
  NOT replicate at 100 nodes, because the 16-node signal is a boundary condition.

  H2 CONFIRMED if: MEK inhibitor median LN_IC50 is not lower than overall median
  (i.e., no MEK sensitivity predicted from near-zero structural position)
  H2 DENIED if: MEK inhibitors are among the most effective drugs in COREAD (would
  contradict the near-zero structural prediction)

### H3: MTOR ANCHOR predicts mTOR inhibitor inefficacy in COREAD
  MTOR z_dr = -2.257 (strongest ANCHOR). Structural prediction: mTOR inhibitors
  (everolimus, temsirolimus) should NOT show strong sensitivity in COREAD — the ANCHOR
  position predicts network normalization (not disruption) upon mTOR inhibition.
  Prediction: median LN_IC50 of mTOR inhibitors is HIGHER than median of EGFR/CDK4
  inhibitors in COREAD.

  H3 CONFIRMED if: mTOR inhibitors less effective (higher LN_IC50) than DAMPER-targeting
  drugs (EGFR, CDK4) in COREAD (one-sided Mann-Whitney p < 0.10)
  H3 DENIED if: mTOR inhibitors equally or more effective than DAMPER-targeting drugs

### H4: EGFR inhibitors sensitive in COREAD (z_dr = +2.411, top DAMPER)
  Direct pharmacological validation of EGFR's structural DAMPER position.
  Prediction: EGFR inhibitors have lower median LN_IC50 in COREAD than in PAAD
  (where EGFR z_dr is NOT the top structural node).
  Secondary: EGFR inhibitors rank in top 30% of drugs by sensitivity in COREAD.

  H4 CONFIRMED if: EGFR inhibitors median LN_IC50 < PAAD median for same drugs
  (direction of effect), AND EGFR inhibitors are in top 50% of drugs by sensitivity
  H4 DENIED if: EGFR inhibitors are not more effective than in PAAD

## Pre-registration caveats

1. MDM2 inhibitors are absent from GDSC2 (confirmed in D12) — MDM2 structural predictions
   are untestable in this dataset. This does not affect H1/H2/H3/H4.
2. BRAF inhibitors (vemurafenib, dabrafenib) target BRAF which is an ANCHOR in CRC
   (z_dr = -1.591). BRAF inhibitors are known to be ineffective in CRC (unlike BRAF-MEL)
   — this is an internally consistent prediction from the structural ANCHOR position.
3. The correlation (H1) is across drugs, not across cell lines. The statistical unit is
   drug (n ≈ 15-20). This is low n; Spearman r = -0.3 requires confirmation with D16+.
4. Some drugs may target multiple proteins. The primary target mapping is fixed above;
   no post-hoc reassignment of drug-target pairs is permitted.
5. LN_IC50 values in GDSC2 are fitted from dose-response curves; very sensitive or
   very resistant cell lines may have LN_IC50 values outside the tested range
   (capped at assay boundary). This is not corrected for in the median.

